# Modulo finance

Escopo
- Entrada/saida de caixa, KPIs financeiros e sugestoes de precificacao.
- Visualizacao de cashflow e top services.

Rotas e entradas
- Stack: `src/modules/finance/presentation/stacks/finance.stack.tsx`.
- Base path: `/finance`.
- Pages:
  - `landing`: `presentation/pages/landing/landing.page`.
  - `home`: `presentation/pages/finance/finance.page`.
  - `services`: `presentation/pages/services-finance/services-finance.page`.
  - `suggestions`: `presentation/pages/suggestions/suggestions.page`.
  - `entries`: `presentation/pages/entries/entries.page`.

Modelos principais (interfaces)
- `FinanceEntryModel`: id, type (income/expense/fixed), amountCents, description, serviceId, date.
- `FinanceQueryModel`: from, to, groupBy, view.
- `FinanceKpiModel`: id, label, value, format, delta.
- `FinanceSeries` + `FinancePoint`: series de pontos.
- `FinanceCashflowRow`: date, description, type, category, amount, status, source, workOrderId, scheduleId.
- `FinanceTopServiceRow`: serviceName, orders, revenue, avgTicket.
- `FinanceDashboardResponseApi`: payload de backend para dashboard.

Services
- `finance.service.ts`
  - Possui mock local de entries (in-memory).
  - `getFinance()` tenta backend via `FinanceApi` e faz fallback para mock.
  - `listServicesWithSuggestions()` usa `CompanyServicesService` para sugerir precos.
  - Converte centavos para valores reais e normaliza percentuais.
- `useFinanceApi()`
  - Hook com cache local para list/create/remove entries.
  - Integra com `MockStoreProvider` para fallback.
- `finance-api.ts`
  - Endpoints: `/finance/dashboard`, `/finance/entries`, `/finance/revenue`, `/finance/internal/entry-types`.
  - Usa `x-workspace-id` quando disponivel.

Integracoes
- Depende de `companyService` (workspaceId).
- Consome `CompanyServiceModel` para sugestoes de precos.
- Pode referenciar `workOrderId` e `scheduleId` em linhas de cashflow.

Guardrails
- Sempre trabalhar em centavos no backend e converter no frontend.
- Garantir `workspaceId` em chamadas que exigem contexto.
- Manter consistencia entre `FinanceEntryType` e UI.
